1. input types in HTML5:
Hidden, Tel, Email, Number, Range, Search, Image, Week, Url, DateTime-Local, Month, Time.

2. how to use the meta tag to provide information about the application name:
`<meta name="application-name" content="OpenStreetMap">`

examples of the application of the input types:
- Hidden: Used to store a value that will not be displayed on the page.
- Tel: Used for a phone number input field.
- Email: Used for an email address input field.
- Number: Used for a numeric input field.
- Range: Used for a slider input field.
- Search: Used for a search input field.
- Image: Used for an image input field, where the user can select an image file to upload.
- Week: Used for a week input field, where the user can select a week from a calendar.
- URL: Used for a URL input field.
- DateTime-Local: Used for a date and time input field.
- Month: Used for a month input field.
- Time: Used for a time input field.
